" {TEXT -1 204 "5.  Three-dimensional plots.  Maple can also provide r
epresentations for graphs of functions of two variables.  The graphs o
f such functions are surfaces in three-dimensional space.  The Maple c
ommand is:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 5 "     " }{TEXT 270 0 "" }{TEXT 271 4 "plot" }{TEXT 272 2 "3d" }
{TEXT -1 2 "( " }{TEXT 273 4 "expr" }{TEXT -1 2 ", " }{TEXT 274 1 "x" 
}{TEXT -1 8 "=range, " }{TEXT 275 0 "" }{TEXT 276 2 "y=" }{TEXT -1 19 
"range [, options]);" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "
" {TEXT -1 6 "where " }{TEXT 277 4 "expr" }{TEXT 281 1 " " }{TEXT -1 
24 "is a symbolic expression" }{TEXT 279 1 " " }{TEXT -1 48 "which rep
resents the function to be plotted and " }{TEXT 278 1 "x" }{TEXT -1 5 
" and " }{TEXT 282 0 "" }{TEXT 283 1 "y" }{TEXT 284 0 "" }{TEXT -1 44 
" are the two independent variables used in  " }{TEXT 280 4 "expr" }
{TEXT -1 25 "  to define the function." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "
" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 4 "The " }{TEXT 285 0 "" }{TEXT 286 6 "pl
ot3d" }{TEXT 287 0 "" }{TEXT -1 238 " command will generate a surface \+
plot for the function over the rectangular range specfied in the comma
nd statement.  The surface plot can be rotated, tipped over and turned
 around to see the surface plot from all side and all viewpoints." }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 278 "For each
 of the following functions provide a plot which shows the graph.  Cho
ose reasonable values for the ranges of x and y.  Rotate, where approp
riate, to present a good view of the graph.  The last two graphs are i
mplicitly defined functions which require the Maple command " }{TEXT 
297 0 "" }{TEXT 298 15 "implicitplot3d " }{TEXT 299 0 "" }{TEXT -1 29 
"which is part of the package " }{TEXT 300 0 "" }{TEXT 301 5 "plots" }
{TEXT 302 0 "" }{TEXT -1 1 "." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 5 "a.   " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "z" "6#%\"zG" }
{TEXT -1 5 " =   " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "cos(2*x-y^2)" "6#-%$cosG6#,&*&\"\"#
\"\"\"%\"xGF)F)*$%\"yGF(!\"\"" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 16 "q:=cos(2*x-z^2);" }}{PARA 
